<TITLE> National IDs are important for citizens: chief justice </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)  The chief justice has said national identity cards are crucial to citizens, which is why the ongoing voter registration should be carried out with care and sincerity. "The nation expects proper voter lists as a prerequisite to holding free and fair elections," Md Ruhul Amin said Friday. "The national identity cards too are also important to the citizens of the country." He made the remark to reporters after volunteering necessary information to the field enumerators visiting at his Hare Road home in the morning to fill out voter information sheets. To a question, he said, "The election litigations should desirably be disposed of as soon as possible." At 10:30am, deputy election commissioner Lutfar Rahman, election officer in charge, Dhaka district Faisal Kader and other EC officials handed the top judge the voter information sheet. Earlier in the morning, the enumerators went to cabinet secretary Ali Imam Majumdar for the same purpose. On Nov 20, door-to-door voter information collection started in 28 police stations in the DCC areas. Photographing and obtaining thumb impression are due to start Dec 1. Citizens will also be simultaneously issued with national IDs. bdnews24.co
